description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reed and Beach Ward, Hammerton Court, Julian Hospital, Norwich. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our male and female inpatient dementia assessment wards are recruiting now!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you take pride in offering a high standard of care for patients, families and carers affected by mental health illness and dementia?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you recognise good practice and want to improve services where possible?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so, then Reed and Beach ward have exciting opportunities for enthusiastic and motivated Clinical Support Workers to join our established inpatient dementia assessment teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a genuine commitment to facilitate a vast spectrum of local training in addition to the standard trust mandatory training and development. You should expect to access all relevant physical health and patient support training to enhance your existing skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We take pride in being a welcoming, talented, friendly and supportive teams who like nothing better than sharing their experiences and learning from each other.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits included with this role are:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS pension&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;a comprehensive in house &amp; external training programmes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;career progression&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;starting annual leave of 27 days per annum increasing to 33 days pa based on length of service (plus paid bank holidays)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;staff physio service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS discounts and many more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please find attached our Job Description and Person Specification for more detail on your Key Accountabilities, then if you feel you have what it takes to genuinely make a difference in peoples lives then please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional contact information&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emma Mertens - Clinical Team Leader Reed Ward – 01603 978310 emma.l.mertens@nsft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Hyde – Acting Clinical Team Leader Beach Ward – 01603 978320 louise.hyde@nsft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
